England lost four late wickets on
the second day of the cricket Test with  Pakistan , and trails by
50 runs in Abu Dhabi.  England finished the day on 207-5. It was on on 198-2
before Alastair Cook was trapped leg-before-wicket by Saeed
Ajmal, who also took the wickets of Kevin Pietersen on 14 and
Eoin Morgan on 3 on the last ball of the session.  Cook and Jonathan Trott combined for 139 runs before Trott
was bowled by Abdur Rehman.  Ian Bell  finished the day unbeaten
on 4.  Pakistan, which leads the series 1-0 after a 10-wicket win
in the opening match, won the toss and elected to bat. Misbah-
ul-Haqâ€™s 84 runs pushed Pakistan to 257 all out. Abdur Rehman,
Ajmal and Junaid Khan were out for no runs, while  Umar Gul 
finished unbeaten but failed to score.  To contact the reporter on this story:
